On Sat, 20 Oct 2001, Steve wrote:

> Ok.  I've stopped for some coffee and a question.  The book says that
> .003 is the low spec for end play with the shims installed.  I've got
> .0025.  The crank is all torqued down and spins like smooth silky
> butter.  Is this still too tight a clearance??

Brand new engine,  I'd probably go with it, if i couldnt get any closer
with what i had on hand.  It will very likely loosen up during breakin.

A used engine?  alreay broken in?  I wouldnt want to run it that tight.

> Also, can I use "used" shims?  Or must I get brand new ones??

Yes, you can use used ones.  Though you may be missing a few ten thou off
of them, as long as they are not bent or warped, and get you in spec,
use'm.

...david (usual disclaimers apply here...this is what I would do if it
